title: For Sale:  first gen pof 556 complete upper
postcontent:
I bought this in 2005 or 2006 when they first came out. I fired less than 100 rounds back then without a hitch, and this past weekend fired about 100 rounds again. 
 
Except this time, there were a few failures to feed properly. I was using a factory PSA lower which i have used withg other uppers flawlessly, and USGI mags which i also successfully used in other weapons. The empty casing would fully leave the weapon, and the bolt face was properly pushing the new round up, but the tip of the bullet would hit, just below the feed ramps in the barrel extension. POF has a lifetime warranty, but i truly do not feel like messing with any of this. This would happen every 10 rounds or so, rapid firing. I think the only issue is that this old style upper does not have the nice m4 feed ramps which would more than correct this issue.
 
On the upper are troy industry shorty sights, designed specifically for this platform. these alone are 200 or so for the pair.
 
asking for 400 for the upper and sights, and maybe it will work fine on your lower? no modifications so the pof warranty is all there.
